Plug-in name: Semantic Constant Folding
Plug-in shortname: scf
Description: propagates constants semantically

Most options of the form '-scf-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-scf-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-scf                pretty print a version of the source code where each
                    constant expression is replaced by its value (opposite
                    option is -no-scf)
-semantic-const-folding  alias for option -scf
-scf-allow-cast     replace expressions by constants even when doing so
                    requires a pointer cast (opposite option is
                    -scf-no-allow-cast)
-cast-from-constant  alias for option -scf-allow-cast
-scf-fct <f1, ..., fn>  propagate constants only into functions f1,...,fn
                    (preferably use -scf-fct="f1, ..., fn")
-semantic-const-fold <f1, ..., fn>  alias for option -scf-fct
-scf-logic          replace values from logical context and create
                    corresponding variables (HIGHLY EXPERIMENTAL) (opposite
                    option is -scf-no-logic)
-semantic-const-fold-logic  alias for option -scf-logic
-scf-project-name <s>  name of the generated project (default is
                    `propagated`) (preferably use -scf-project-name="")

*** DEBUG

-scf-debug <n>      level of debug for plug-in Semantic Constant Folding
                    (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-scf-help           help of plug-in Semantic Constant Folding
-scf-h              alias for option -scf-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-scf-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Semantic Constant Folding
                    to a file. <K> is a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -scf-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-scf-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -scf-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -scf-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-scf-verbose <n>    level of verbosity for plug-in Semantic Constant Folding
                    (default to 1)
-scf-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1>
                    to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -scf-warn-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -scf-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
